TITLE: Merging BootstrapSetup with Other Setup Classes in Akka.NET
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a BootstrapSetup with HOCON configuration and merge it with other Setup classes (in this case SerializationSetup) to create an ActorSystemSetup object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/configuration/config.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var config = ConfigurationFactory.ParseString(@"""
akka.actor{
    serializers{
        hyperion = ""Akka.Serialization.HyperionSerializer, Akka.Serialization.Hyperion""
    }
}""");

// sets up the ActorSystem with both the bootstrap configuration
// settings we need for DI plus the programmatic serialization
var bootstrap = BootstrapSetup.Create().WithConfig(config);
var serializationSetup = SerializationSetup.Create(system => {
    // we'll use Hyperion to serialize all of our messages
    system.Serialization.AddSerializer("hyperion", new SerializerDetails(
        typeof(HyperionSerializer),
        "hyperion",
        new[] { typeof(IActorRef) }
    ));
});

var actorSystemSetup = bootstrap.And(serializationSetup);
```

