TITLE: Creating Reusable Partial Graph Component in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a reusable partial graph component using GraphDSL.Create(). It returns a FlowShape, allowing the component to be used in both complex graph constructions and simpler linear DSLs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/modularitycomposition.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var partial = GraphDsl.Create(builder =>
{
    var b = builder.Add(new Broadcast<int>(2));
    var c = builder.Add(new Merge<int>(2));
    var e = builder.Add(new Balance<int>(2));
    var f = builder.Add(new Merge<int>(2));

    builder.To(c).From(f);
    builder.From(b).Via(c).To(f);
    builder.From(b).Via(Flow.Create<int>().Select(x => x + 1)).Via(e).To(f);

    return new FlowShape<int, int>(b.In, e.Out(1));
}).Named("partial");
```

