TITLE: Creating a Flow with Global Rate Limiter in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a Flow that uses the global limiter actor. It utilizes SelectAsync and the Ask pattern with a timeout to control the flow rate.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/cookbook.md#2025-04-16_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public Flow<T, T, NotUsed> LimitGlobal<T>(IActorRef limiter, TimeSpan maxAllowedWait)
  => Flow.Create<T>().SelectAsync(4, element =>
  {
      var limiterTriggerTask = limiter.Ask<T>(WantToPass.Instance, maxAllowedWait);
      return limiterTriggerTask.ContinueWith(t => element);
  });
```

