TITLE: Word Count using Akka.NET Streams
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a basic word count operation using Akka.NET Streams. It groups words, counts their occurrences, and merges the results into a single output stream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/cookbook.md#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var words = Source.Empty<string>();
var counts = words
    // split the words into separate streams first
    .GroupBy(MaximumDistinctWords, x => x)
    //transform each element to pair with number of words in it
    .Select(x => Tuple.Create(x, 1))
    // add counting logic to the streams
    .Sum((l, r) => Tuple.Create(l.Item1, l.Item2 + r.Item2))
    // get a stream of word counts
    .MergeSubstreams();
```

