TITLE: Implementing Actor with Factory Method Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement an actor with constructor parameters using the recommended factory method pattern for Props creation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/actors/untyped-actor-api.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public class DemoActor : UntypedActor
{
    private readonly int _magicNumber;

    public DemoActor(int magicNumber)
    {
        _magicNumber = magicNumber;
    }

    protected override void OnReceive(object message)
    {
        if (message is int x)
        {
            Sender.Tell(x + _magicNumber);
        }
    }

    public static Props Props(int magicNumber)
    {
        return Akka.Actor.Props.Create(() => new DemoActor(magicNumber));
    }
}

system.ActorOf(DemoActor.Props(42), "demo");
```

