TITLE: Creating Complex RunnableGraph with GraphDSL in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a complex, non-linear stream processing network using Akka.NET's GraphDSL. It includes fan-in, fan-out stages, and directed cycles, showcasing the flexibility of the graph-based approach.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/modularitycomposition.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
RunnableGraph.FromGraph(GraphDsl.Create(builder =>
{
    var a = builder.Add(Source.Single(0)).Outlet;
    var b = builder.Add(new Broadcast<int>(2));
    var c = builder.Add(new Merge<int>(2));
    var d = builder.Add(Flow.Create<int>().Select(x => x + 1));
    var e = builder.Add(new Balance<int>(2));
    var f = builder.Add(new Merge<int>(2));
    var g = builder.Add(Sink.ForEach<int>(Console.WriteLine)).Inlet;

    builder.To(c).From(f);
    builder.From(a).Via(b).Via(c).To(f);
    builder.From(b).Via(d).Via(e).To(f);
    builder.From(e).To(g);

    return ClosedShape.Instance;
}));
```

