TITLE: Triggering Flow with ZipWith Operation in Akka.NET Streams
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to trigger the flow of elements using `ZipWith` in Akka.NET Streams. `ZipWith` avoids creating a tuple by directly applying a function that returns the desired output when a message and trigger are available.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/cookbook.md#2025-04-16_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var graph = RunnableGraph.FromGraph(GraphDsl.Create(b =>
{
    var zip = b.Add(ZipWith.Apply((Message msg, Trigger trigger) => msg));

    b.From(elements).To(zip.In0);
    b.From(triggerSource).To(zip.In1);
    b.From(zip.Out).To(sink);

    return ClosedShape.Instance;
}));
```

