TITLE: Breaking Back-Pressure Cycles in Akka Streams TCP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to break back-pressure cycles in client-server scenarios by injecting an initial message from the server side.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/workingwithstreamingio.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var welcomeMessage = Source.Single(ByteString.FromString("Welcome to the Akka TCP Server!\n"));

var commandHandler = Flow.Create<ByteString>()
    .Merge(welcomeMessage)
    .Via(Framing.Delimiter(
        ByteString.FromString("\n"),
        256,
        allowTruncation: true))
    .TakeWhile(text => !text.ToString().Contains("BYE"))
    .Concat(Source.Single(ByteString.FromString("BYE\n")))
    .Map(text => ByteString.FromString("Server: " + text + "\n"));

var serverLogic = Sink.ForEach<Tcp.IncomingConnection>(connection =>
    connection.HandleWith(commandHandler, materializer));

var binding = Tcp.Get(system).Bind(endpoint).RunWith(serverLogic, materializer);
```

