TITLE: Combining Sources Using the Simplified API in Akka.NET (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet describes how to combine multiple sources into one using the simplified API in Akka.NET. It merges two sources into a single stream and aggregates their values. Akka.NET dependencies and a materializer are necessary for running the combined stream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/workingwithgraphs.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var sourceOne = Source.Single(1);
var sourceTwo = Source.Single(2);
var merged = Source.Combine(sourceOne, sourceTwo, i => new Merge<int, int>(i));

var mergedResult = merged.RunWith(Sink.Aggregate<int, int>(0, (agg, i) => agg + i), materializer);
```

