TITLE: Using System-Level Materializer in Akka.NET Actor
DESCRIPTION: This alternative solution uses the ActorSystem's materializer, which is cached internally and managed by the system. This approach avoids having to manually dispose of the materializer while still preventing the creation of multiple instances.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/debugging/rules/AK2002.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using Akka.Actor;
using Akka.Streams;
using Akka.Streams.Dsl;

public sealed class MyActor : ReceiveActor
{
    public MyActor()
    {
        ReceiveAsync<string>(
            s => s == "hello",
            async _ =>
            {
                await Source.Single(1)
                    .Select(x => x + 1)
                    .ToMaterialized(Sink.ForEach<int>(_ => { }), Keep.Right)
                    .Run(Context.System.Materializer()); // Use ActorSystem.Materializer(), this is cached internally
            });
    }
}
```

