TITLE: Defining SQL Query for Retrieving Persistent Events by ID in Akka.Persistence
DESCRIPTION: SQL query statement used to retrieve events from a SQLite journal by persistence ID within a specified sequence number range. The query orders results by sequence number to ensure proper event ordering during replay.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/persistence/custom-persistence-provider.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
public const string ByPersistenceIdSql = @"
    select
        j.persistence_id as PersistenceId,
        j.sequence_nr as SequenceNr,
        j.is_deleted as IsDeleted,
        j.manifest as Manifest,
        j.payload as Payload,
        j.created_at as Timestamp
    from journal j
    where j.persistence_id = @PersistenceId
      and j.sequence_nr >= @FromSequenceNr
      and j.sequence_nr <= @ToSequenceNr
    order by j.sequence_nr
    limit @MaxCount;"
```

