TITLE: Using Predicates in Message Handlers in C#
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of predicates to conditionally handle messages. Handlers for strings with length greater than specified values are defined. Only the first handler with a true predicate is invoked. Examples illustrate message outcomes based on different string lengths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/src/core/Akka/Util/MatchHandler/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
Receive<string>(s => s.Length>5, s => Console.WriteLine("Received string: " + s);
Receive<string>(s => s.Length>5, s => Console.WriteLine("1: " + s));    //1
Receive<string>(s => s.Length>2, s => Console.WriteLine("2: " + s));    //2
Receive<string>(s => Console.WriteLine("3: " + s));                     //3
```

