TITLE: Closing TCP Connections in Akka Streams
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to close incoming TCP connections by cancelling the flow or shutting down the server's socket.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/streams/workingwithstreamingio.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var connections = Tcp.Get(system).Bind(endpoint);
var closed = connections.To(Sink.ForEach<IncomingConnection>(conn =>
    conn.HandleWith(Flow.FromSinkAndSource<ByteString, ByteString>(
        Sink.Cancelled,
        Source.Empty<ByteString>()), materializer)));

closed.Run(materializer);
```

