TITLE: Constructor Pattern Matching with Typed Pattern in C# 7
DESCRIPTION: This C# 7 code demonstrates pattern matching using a switch statement and a 'when' clause to simulate constructor patterns. It checks the type of the input 'x' and then uses the 'when' clause to check properties.  It returns a string based on the matched case. Relies on `Person` and `Dog` classes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/community/contributing/porting-guide.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: c#
CODE:
```
public string TestPattern(object x)
{
    switch(x)
    {
        case Person p when p.LastName == "Alexander": return $"found an Alexander, first name = {p.FirstName}";
        case Dog d when d.Name == "Suka": return "found a dog named Suka";  
    }
    return string.Empty;
}
```

