TITLE: Recommended Pattern: Using PersistAll() After a Loop in Akka.NET
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates the recommended approach where events are collected in a collection inside the loop, then persisted in a single batch using PersistAll() after the loop completes. This improves performance by batching database operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/akkadotnet/akka.net/blob/dev/docs/articles/debugging/rules/AK1006.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using Akka.Persistence;

public class MyActor: ReceivePersistentActor
{
    public override string PersistenceId { get; }
    public MyActor(string persistenceId)
    {
        PersistenceId = persistenceId;
        CommandAny(obj =>
        {
            var events = new List<int>();
            for (var i=0; i<10; i++)
            {
                events.Add(i);
            }
            PersistAll(events, o => {});
        });
    }
}
```

